    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plastic laminate made by bonding layers of cloth or paper with a resin under heat and pressure; made in sheet, rod, and tube form, and in other molded shapes. May be used to refer to the trademarked product and to similar materials.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Marca registrada para un tipo de laminado plástico comercialmente producido y constituido al unir capas de tela o papel mediante una resina y bajo calor y presión. Realizado en forma de láminas, varillas y tubos, entre otras formas moldeadas.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Handelsmerk voor een soort commercieel geproduceerd plastic laminaat dat wordt gemaakt door lagen stof of papier bij hoge temperaturen en onder druk te hechten met hars; wordt vervaardigd in de vorm van platen, staven en buizen of andere vormen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以加溫和加壓的方式，用樹脂黏合多層布料或紙而成之塑膠疊層。製成板狀、桿狀和管狀，以及其它形式。可用指經商標註冊之產品及相似之材料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
